#Ava

#### Look through Ava's emails below and see which ones might be legit and which might be phishing attacks.


<div style="font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6;">



  <hr>

  <p><strong>Message A – Text</strong></p>
  <p>
    Hey Ava — quick thing: it’s Jess from chem class. I’m helping run the Homecoming raffle and need to double-check the list.<br><br>
    You bought a ticket at lunch last week, right? Can you send me the email you used so I can confirm your entry?
  </p>

  <hr>

  <p><strong>Message B – Email</strong></p>
  <p><em>Subject:</em> <strong>Portland Food Truck Fest – Lost Item Report</strong></p>
  <p>
    Hi Ava,<br><br>
    This is the Portland Food Truck Fest volunteer desk. Someone turned in a wallet matching your description (photo ID inside says “Ava Rivera”).<br><br>
    To return it, we need to confirm your mailing address and phone number.<br><br>
    Please complete the form here: <a href="#">pdxfoodfest.com-verify.info</a><br><br>
    You can also call the desk at (503) 872-4182 if you have questions. We’ll hold the item for 48 hours before sending it to lost property.<br><br>
    Thanks,<br>
    <em>The Volunteer Team</em>
  </p>

  <hr>

  <p><strong>Message C – Instagram DM</strong></p>
  <p>
    Hey Ava! We’re finalizing the last wave of Taylor Swift pre-show volunteers in Portland.<br><br>
    You’d help greet guests + hand out wristbands. As thanks, you’d get free merch and early entry.<br><br>
    If you’re interested, send:<br>
    - Name & birthday<br>
    - Cell number<br>
    - Preferred T-shirt size<br><br>
    Just need it tonight to lock in your spot. We’ll text you the details tomorrow!
  </p>

</div>

MARKDOWN
